sentences: Richard Edison Uy Yap (born May 18, 1967) is a Filipino actor, singer, model and businessman of Chinese descent.
In 2011, Yap launched his career in ABS-CBN via My Binondo Girl where he played Kim Chiu's father, Chen Sy.
In 2012, Yap played a recurring character in Walang Hanggan as Henry de Dios.
The show ran from 2012 to 2014 due to its large following and loyal fanbase.
He topbilled the 2016 installment of Regal Films' Mano Po 7: Chinoy.
On December 16, 2020, he signed his management contract with GMA Artist Center.
Yap was a candidate for representative of Cebu City's north district in the 2019 elections.
He is running again for the same congressional seat in the 2022 elections, this time under the National Unity Party.
– 2013 She's the One (Film) (performer: "Don't Know What to Do, Don't Know What to Say")
– 2012 Be Careful with My Heart (TV Series) (performer – 1 episode)
– Maya Is Determined to Chase Her Dreams (2012) ...
In 1993, he married Melody Yap, with whom he has two children, Ashley and Dylan.
Running under BARUG-PDP–Laban, he failed to unseat the incumbent Raul del Mar. Yap finished second out of four candidates.
Coming from a family who loves to cook, Richard aspired a to be chef in his younger years.
